The paper deals with spectrum management and resource allocation problems in wireless communications and computer networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper proposes a deep autoencoder network for solving linear sum assignment problems, which is a combinatorial optimization problem, using machine learning techniques. This makes the paper relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses conditional variational autoencoders, which are a type of generative neural network, to solve the optimization problem, making it relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
